│ constant-foldable expressions (mul by 0, urem with 0, smax with identical operands) and unreachable code paths. The VPlan cost model correctly identifies │
│ these optimizations and determines scalar execution is optimal, while the legacy cost model overestimates vectorization benefits. However,                │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications() fails to detect these as 'additional simplifications' because it only checks for missing instructions in the      │
